\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Mapping between two polarisation-encoded qubits undergoing a polarising beamsplitter (PBS) operation, and its equivalent representation using 4 time-bins in a pulse-train. The PBS completely reflects (transmits) the vertical (horizontal) polarisations. The evolution of the four logical basis states, and their respective outputs, are shown explicitly. Writing out this PBS transformation in matrix form yields a permutation. Taking this permutation and relabelling the modes, we obtain the time-bin transformation shown underneath -- a simple swap of two of the four time-bins.}}{9}{figure.5}}
\newlabel{fig:PBS_TB}{{5}{9}{Mapping between two polarisation-encoded qubits undergoing a polarising beamsplitter (PBS) operation, and its equivalent representation using 4 time-bins in a pulse-train. The PBS completely reflects (transmits) the vertical (horizontal) polarisations. The evolution of the four logical basis states, and their respective outputs, are shown explicitly. Writing out this PBS transformation in matrix form yields a permutation. Taking this permutation and relabelling the modes, we obtain the time-bin transformation shown underneath -- a simple swap of two of the four time-bins}{figure.5}{}}
